  "prompt": "How to reset Honeywell thermostat and erase schedule?",
  "response": "To reset a Honeywell thermostat and erase its schedule, the steps can vary depending on the model. Below are general instructions that should work for most Honeywell thermostats. If these steps don\u2019t match your model, refer to the user manual for specific instructions.\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Reset and Erase Schedule:**\n\n1. **Access the Menu:**\n   - Turn on the thermostat and press the **Menu** or **Settings** button.\n\n2. **Navigate to Reset Options:**\n   - Look for an option like **Reset**, **Factory Reset**, or **Restore Defaults**. This is usually found in the **Settings** or **Advanced Settings** menu.\n\n3. **Select Reset Type:**\n   - Some models allow you to reset specific settings (e.g., schedule, Wi-Fi, or all settings). Choose **Reset Schedule** or **Factory Reset** to erase the schedule and other settings.\n\n4. **Confirm the Reset:**\n   - Confirm your selection when prompted. The thermostat will erase the schedule and restore default settings.\n\n5. **Reconfigure Settings (Optional):**\n   - After resetting, you can set up a new schedule or adjust other preferences.\n\n---\n\n### **For Non-Programmable Thermostats:**\nIf your thermostat is non-programmable, it may not have a schedule. To reset it:\n   - Turn off the power to the thermostat (via the circuit breaker or HVAC system).\n   - Wait a few minutes, then turn the power back on. This will reset the thermostat to its default settings.\n\n---\n\n### **For Wi-Fi Connected Thermostats (e.g., Honeywell Home T9/T10):**\n   - Open the **Honeywell Home app** on your phone.\n   - Navigate to **Settings** > **Reset** or **Restore Defaults**.\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to reset the thermostat and clear the schedule.\n\n---\n\n### **Manual Reset (For Older Models):**\nIf the thermostat has a reset button (usually on the back or side):\n   - Remove the thermostat from the wall.\n   - Press and hold the reset button for 5-10 seconds.\n   - Reinstall the thermostat.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n- Resetting the thermostat will erase all customizations, including schedules, Wi-Fi settings, and preferences.\n- If you\u2019re unsure about your thermostat model, check the **Honeywell website** or user manual for specific instructions.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
